<% content_for :title, "TheraSaurus Privacy Policy" %>
<% content_for :head do %>
  <meta name="description" content="Privacy policy for TheraSaurus.">
<% end %>

<article class="w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto rounded-xl bg-white p-8 shadow-lg">
  <%= image_tag "logo.svg", alt: "TheraSaurus", class: "h-16 w-auto mb-8" %>

  <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-plum mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Effective Date: May 14, 2026</p>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">What TheraSaurus does</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      TheraSaurus helps pediatric therapists create and manage public profiles so families can find care more easily.
      TheraSaurus is not a healthcare provider, does not provide therapy, and does not provide emergency or crisis services.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Information we collect</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      We collect information needed to create accounts, operate therapist profiles, process memberships, protect the service,
      and respond to support requests. This may include:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      <li>Account information, such as name, email address, sign-in provider, and account status.</li>
      <li>Profile information, such as profession, credentials, education, specialties, services, languages, practice details, profile photos, addresses, phone numbers, websites, insurance selections, fees, availability, and profile copy.</li>
      <li>Credential review information, such as credential details and uploaded credential documents.</li>
      <li>Billing information, such as Stripe customer, subscription, checkout, invoice, and payment status data. We do not store full card numbers.</li>
      <li>Technical information, such as IP address, browser details, device details, request logs, security events, and error reports.</li>
      <li>Messages you send to us, such as support emails, feature requests, and write-in requests.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">How we use information</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      <li>To create and manage therapist accounts.</li>
      <li>To publish eligible public profiles and directory search results.</li>
      <li>To process memberships, free trials, billing, and subscription changes.</li>
      <li>To send account, billing, credential, security, and service emails.</li>
      <li>To review credentials and keep profile information accurate.</li>
      <li>To prevent abuse, debug errors, monitor uptime, and protect the service.</li>
      <li>To respond to support requests and improve TheraSaurus.</li>
      <li>To comply with legal obligations.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Public profile information</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      If your profile is eligible to be public, information you enter for your public profile may be shown to visitors and search engines.
      Do not add information to your public profile that you do not want made public.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Google sign-in</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      Google sign-in is optional. If you use it, Google helps confirm your identity and sends basic account information needed for sign-in,
      such as your email address. TheraSaurus does not use Google sign-in to access your Google Drive, Gmail, Calendar, or contacts.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">How we share information</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      We share information only when needed to operate TheraSaurus, publish eligible profile information, comply with the law,
      or complete a transaction you request. This may include sharing information with:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      <li>Service providers for hosting, database, authentication, storage, email delivery, monitoring, logging, security, and support.</li>
      <li>Stripe for checkout, payment processing, subscription management, invoices, tax calculation, and customer portal access.</li>
      <li>Google when you choose Google sign-in.</li>
      <li>Visitors and search engines when your profile is public.</li>
      <li>Law enforcement, courts, regulators, or other parties when required by law or needed to protect rights, safety, or security.</li>
      <li>A buyer or successor if TheraSaurus is involved in a merger, acquisition, financing, or sale of assets.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      We do not sell personal information for money. We do not currently use cross-site behavioral advertising.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Cookies and similar technology</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      TheraSaurus uses cookies and similar technology for sign-in, session security, checkout, fraud prevention, and basic service operation.
      You can control cookies through your browser, but disabling required cookies may prevent sign-in or checkout from working.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Health information and HIPAA</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      TheraSaurus is not intended to store client health records, patient messages, treatment notes, or emergency information.
      Do not submit client protected health information to TheraSaurus unless a separate written agreement allows it.
      Therapists are responsible for their own healthcare privacy obligations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Security and retention</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      We use technical and administrative safeguards intended to protect information. No internet service is perfectly secure.
      We keep information as long as needed to provide the service, comply with legal duties, resolve disputes, collect fees,
      prevent abuse, and keep business records.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Your choices</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      You can review and update most account and profile information from your account. You can also contact us to request access,
      correction, deletion, or export of your personal information. We may need to verify your identity before acting on a request,
      and some information may need to be retained when required by law or for legitimate business reasons.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Children</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      TheraSaurus accounts are intended for therapists and other adults who can enter a binding agreement.
      We do not knowingly collect account information from children under 13.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Changes</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      We may update this Privacy Policy when the service changes or legal requirements change. The effective date above shows when this page was last updated.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8 border-t border-border-default pt-6">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">Contact</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-7 text-text-body">
      Email
      <%= mail_to "support@therasaurus.org",
        "support@therasaurus.org",
        class: "font-semibold text-plum hover:underline focus-visible:underline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-plum rounded cursor-pointer" %>
      with privacy questions or requests.
    </p>
  </section>
</article>
